him away, and delivered him to Pontius Pilate the governor.","year":33},{"id":"recEalvo5E16wPS0t","ref":"Matt.27.3","text":"Then Judas, which had betrayed him, when he saw that he was condemned, repented himself, and brought again the thirty pieces of silver to the chief priests and elders,","year":33},{"id":"recoEokOT6iHuFXP3","ref":"Matt.27.4","text":"Saying, I have sinned in that I have betrayed the innocent blood. And they said, What is that to us? see thou to that.","year":33},{"id":"recORP3WRlv6DSNu3","ref":"Matt.27.5","text":"And he cast down the pieces of silver in the temple, and departed, and went and hanged himself.","year":33},{"id":"recdrYzN0WQgWcMor","ref":"Matt.27.6","text":"And the chief priests took the silver pieces, and said, It is not lawful for to put them into the treasury, because it is the price of blood.","year":33},{"id":"recSx131aHYJXMeGM","ref":"Matt.27.7","text":"And they took counsel, and bought with them the potter’s field, to bury strangers in.","year":33},{"id":"recPiFAPx1jjA2Tpp","ref":"Matt.27.8","text":"Wherefore that field was called, The field of blood, unto this day.","year":33}]}
